# Tammam Properties — Real Estate MVP

Stack: Next.js + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS, Supabase (Postgres + Storage)

Quick start:
1. Create a Supabase project and copy NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL, NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY.
2. Create a bucket named `property-images` in Supabase Storage.
3. Run the SQL in `schema.sql` using Supabase SQL editor.
4. Create a `.env.local` from `.env.example` and fill keys.
5. npm install && npm run dev

Note: Do NOT commit secrets. Keep `.env.local` out of the repo.

Important env vars used by the app:
- NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
- NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
- SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY (server-side only)
- ADMIN_SECRET (server-side only)
- NEXT_PUBLIC_ADMIN_SECRET (client-side used to send admin requests)
- NEXT_PUBLIC_ADMIN_WHATSAPP (for client-side WhatsApp link, digits only or with +)
- NEXT_PUBLIC_ADMIN_EMAIL (optional mailto link)
- OPENAI_API_KEY (optional to enable AI generation on approve)

Routes of interest:
- /                — home list of published properties
- /add             — public "أضف عقارك" form (submits as pending)
- /properties/:id  — property details
- /admin           — admin review board (approve/reject)

APIs:
- POST /api/properties             — create submission (public)
- POST /api/properties/attach-image — attach uploaded image URL to property (server-side insert)
- POST /api/admin/properties/:id/approve — approve (x-admin-secret header required)
- POST /api/admin/properties/:id/reject  — reject (x-admin-secret header required)
- POST /api/admin/properties/:id/update  — update property fields (x-admin-secret required)

